---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="About — Stryda"
  description="Why Stryda exists, who we serve, and how we work with the first ten boutiques."
>
  <section class="sec-first">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1 class="h-1" style="margin-top: var(--s-4); max-width: 22ch;">
        Boutique sell-side deserves great tooling.
      </h1>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--s-7); font-size: 18px; max-width: 60ch;">
        Big banks have internal AI teams and seven-figure tooling budgets. Boutiques run on associates, late nights, and prior CIMs. We are building the missing layer &mdash; workflow, not chatbot &mdash; so a five-person shop ships work that competes with a fifty-person one.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sec">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Why us</p>
          <h2 class="h-2" style="margin-top: var(--s-4); max-width: 18ch;">
            A copilot built by people who have done the job.
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="stack">
          <p>Sell-side mandates are mechanical at the edges and judgment-heavy in the middle. The mechanical edges &mdash; financial extraction, draft writing, buyer research &mdash; are the part AI is best at and the part bankers spend the most time on. Closing that gap is what Stryda exists to do.</p>
          <p>We talk to associates and partners weekly. We ship features they ask for. We do not ship features they don't. Every line of copy on this site, every module in the product, traces back to a conversation with a banker working a real mandate.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sec">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">What we believe</p>
          <h2 class="h-2" style="margin-top: var(--s-4); max-width: 14ch;">
            Three things we will not do.
          </h2>
        </div>
        <ol class="dash-list">
          <li><strong>No black-box numbers.</strong> Every figure in every output traces back to its source. No "trust the model." If a banker can't defend it in a diligence call, it doesn't ship.</li>
          <li><strong>No cross-tenant anything.</strong> Your deal data does not train our model. Your deal data does not show up in retrieval for another tenant. The boundary is enforced in the architecture, not the policy doc.</li>
          <li><strong>No enterprise-sales theatre.</strong> Free for ninety days. Real mandates. The associate decides. If the product is not pulling its weight after two deals, we want to know &mdash; and we want you to walk.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sec">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Design partner program</p>
          <h2 class="h-2" style="margin-top: var(--s-4); max-width: 14ch;">
            Ten boutiques. Three at a time.
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="stack">
          <p>We are onboarding ten boutiques in cohorts of three. Each design partner is free for ninety days, runs at least two real mandates through the system, and meets weekly with the founding team for a thirty-minute feedback call. We sit next to your associates while they use the product. We capture every breakage and every wish.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <table class="tbl">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>What you get</th>
            <th>What we ask</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Full product, all modules, ninety days free</td>
            <td>Two real sell-side mandates run through Stryda</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Onboarding support, week one</td>
            <td>Thirty minutes weekly with the founding team</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Direct line to engineers fixing what breaks</td>
            <td>Tell us when it breaks, even when it's awkward</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Every feature request tracked, prioritized, replied to</td>
            <td>Convert at $2&ndash;3k per month after day ninety, or walk</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <div style="margin-top: var(--s-8); display: flex; gap: var(--s-5); flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/demo" class="btn">Request a demo</a>
        <a href="mailto:bobbyzli@berkeley.edu" class="btn-link">Email founders</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sec">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Where we are</p>
          <h2 class="h-2" style="margin-top: var(--s-4); max-width: 14ch;">
            Founded 2026. San Francisco.
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="stack">
          <p>Small founding team. Live design-partner cohort. Software shipping weekly. If you advise on lower-middle-market sell-side deals or you back vertical AI for regulated workflows, we'd like to hear from you.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
